# Exploration: stat

## Test scope
  128 behavioral groups: 111 unique, 17 shared

  Contexts referenced in exemplars below:
    words_minimal: 1500 English words; input.txt + other.txt
    words_standard: 1500 English words; files, hidden, subdir, symlink, executable, readonly

## Observed: 7/7 flags
  4 uniquely observable, 3 distinguishable via flag pairs
  1 behavioral aliases (different flags, identical behavior)
  robustness: 10 verified in all contexts, 0 in most, 0 context-dependent

Aliases: -L = --dereference, -f = --file-system, -t = --terse

## Unique behavior (observable when tested alone)
  --cached  # specify how to use cached attributes; useful on remote file systems
    tested: "--cached=default" "input.txt" in words_minimal
    | stdout: 8 lines
    | exit 0
    without flag:
    with flag:
        File: input.txt
        Size: 10586     	Blocks: 24         IO Block: 4096   regular file
      Device: 254,0	Inode: 148635664   Links: 1
      Access: (0644/-rw-r--r--)  Uid: ( 1000/mmontalbo)   Gid: (  100/   users)
      Access: 2026-05-14 12:40:44.573643807 -0700
      Modify: 2026-05-14 12:40:44.573643807 -0700
            ... (2 more)
  --format
    tested: "--format=%s" "input.txt" "other.txt" in words_minimal
    | flag adds 2 lines: 10586, 12
    | flag removes 16 lines:   File: input.txt,   Size: 10586     	Blocks: 24         IO Block: 4096   regular file, Device: 254,0	Inode: 148638233   Links: 1, Access: (0644/-rw-r--r--)  Uid: ( 1000/mmontalbo)   Gid: (  100/   users), Access: 2026-05-14 12:40:44.576102500 -0700
    without flag:
        File: input.txt
        Size: 10586     	Blocks: 24         IO Block: 4096   regular file
      Device: 254,0	Inode: 148638233   Links: 1
      Access: (0644/-rw-r--r--)  Uid: ( 1000/mmontalbo)   Gid: (  100/   users)
      Access: 2026-05-14 12:40:44.576102500 -0700
      Modify: 2026-05-14 12:40:44.576102500 -0700
            ... (10 more)
    with flag:
      10586
      12
  --printf  # like --format, but interpret backslash escapes, and do not output a mandatory trailing newline; if you want a newline, include \n in FORMAT
